commitResults.messageBody:
Companies, Events, and Persons all have some common attributes
and methods (e.g. name, tags, isSameEntry()).

Creating a generic Entry class and converting UniquePersonList
into UniqueEntryList that can hold any child class of Entry
allows Companies and Events to be added into the existing
infrastructure while reusing as much of the existing code as
possible.

Let's
* create a Entry class that Person inherits from and contains
the aforementioned common attributes and methods
* convert UniquePersonList into a UniqueEntryList that can hold
any child class of Entry.
* convert the Person-specific exceptions into general Entry
exceptions

commitResults.messageBody:
The app did not have an edit company command. There was also some
unnecessary repetition in the code between each of the edit commands.

To fix this, a new EditCompanyCommand is added. The parseTags()
function was also taken out of the code of each of the edit command
parsers and instead stored in ParserUtil to facilitate code reuse.
Similarly, the MESSAGE_NOT_EDITED is instead stored in
commons.core.Messages since it is used by all 3 edit commands.

* add the EditEventCommand
* move parseTags() to ParserUtil
* move MESSAGE_NOT_EDITED to commons.core.messages

Note: The code to edit all instances of companyNames in events/persons
whose companyName matches the name of the company before it was edited
has not been implemented.
